Much worse could have happened with anti-CAA protesters: BJP leader Dilip Ghosh

Jan 31, 2020, 09:53AM IST

Source: Times Now

West Bengal BJP chief Dilip Ghosh stoked a fresh controversy, saying that the protesters can stage their protest in gardens and circuses as there are a lot of other places. He said that they should be thankful to their stars as "much worse could have happened" with them. The BJP leader said, " Much worse could have happened. There are a lot of gardens, circuses for staging protests. Why do they come near our workers? to make news or be martyred." The protesters had shown black flags to the BJP chief during a pro-CAA rally.